Asia
---
India
- Kerala state. 15 Aug 2021. (Conf) 66 cases; Outbreak declared over. The 1st case was confirmed in a 24-year-old pregnant woman on the outskirts of the capital on 8 Jul 2021. At least 13 health workers in a private hospital in the city tested positive subsequently. Of the 66 cases, at least 62 were from the capital district, 2 from Ernakulam, and one each from Kottayam and Kollam districts.
https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/kerala-declares-zika-outbreak-under-control/article35922267.ece/
[HealthMap/ProMED map of India: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8599994,304]

